ğŸ” This approach uses -webkit-line-clamp to truncate to 2 lines (multi-line ellipsis). Itâ€™s well-supported in modern browsers.

<style>
  .comment-cell {
    max-width: 250px;
    display: -webkit-box;
    -webkit-line-clamp: 2;     /* Limit to 2 lines */
    -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
    white-space: normal;
    line-height: 1.2em;
    height: 2.4em;
    cursor: help;
  }
</style>


